                        <seg type="docType">Fine.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116122">Netherton (Northumberland)</placeName>. <origDate when="1283">Morrow of St. Hilary, 11 Ed. I (1283). </origDate>. Fine made in the court of the Bishop of Durham, at Durham, on the morrow of St. Hilary, 11 Ed. I, and 9th year of Bishop Rob. de Lisle, between Alan de Slykeburn and Agnes his wife, plaintiffs, and Robert, son of Henry de Estslykeburn, and Eva his wife, defendants, concerning one messuage, 44 acres of land, and 2 1/2 acres of meadow in Nedderton, by which the said Robert and Eva acknowledge the said tenement to be the right of Alan and Agnes, also they grant that all the tenements which Alice de Ravensworth, who was the wife of Robert, brother of the said Eva, held in dowry, in the village of Nedderton, shall after the death of the said Alice, remain to Alan and Agnes for ever. For this grant Alan gave to the said Robert and Eve 28 acres of land in Estslykeburn.</p>
